node.text:
Today I completed a 30 day streak on @gozwift - not planned and completely unintentional.
.
As I moved into working from home I started doing an hour on the turbo before I logged on to work to continue with some sense of normality and so it wasn‚Äôt such a shock to the system when it was time to go back.  Clearly no one knew how long this situation would last and that continues to be the case.
.
So how do I feel after 30 days? Well my washing line is always full of bib shorts, I thought the Wringer workout was the worst one until I did the Roubaix - ouch!  I have heavy and tired legs!  But I‚Äôm not hating the turbo which is a victory in my book!
.
In the 30 days I have covered 785km/487 miles - now someone pass me the pimms for this afternoon üçπ .

node.text:
Yesterday I marshalled at the @ocrwc and had a blast! The day started on site at 5:30am and finished at 6:30pm.  As marshals were being picked up at the end of the day we collect the marshals along the route and at the spinning monkey obstacle this father and son team were trying to keep their bands.  The son got across and no pressure but the dad had a group of us in support.  You can hear the cheer as he completed the obstacle üôåüèª
Shout out to the @ocrwc team, the @nuclearraces team, @nuclearphoenixocr who were all awesome, @jonalbon @ryanatkinsdiet @ocr_unicorn @ocrkarin @spartansoz @spartan_scotty amongst many who were awesome and great to see you all in action! Of course all the @ukmuddqueens especially @emilyredadventure who is just epic, @dave.a_ocr @d_j_w87 @ebc_bri @geek1066 who were all great and @bamma_ocr my neighbour marshal!
You are all inspiring!

node.text:
After 8 amazing stages of @letourfemmes I cannot wait to get my new bike and get back out on two wheels! What an advert for women‚Äôs cycling it has been to have a women‚Äôs tour!
.
Stage 7 performance from @annemiekvanvleuten with insane climbing and power shown in her numbers.  And then she did the same on stage 8 (including numerous bike changes üòù)!
.
The crowds were amazing, the TV exposure and this is what years of campaigning by many has come to.  The progress, the visibility and continuing with this to make this the norm.
.
Totally inspirational üíõ especially for the next generation - all the young girls thinking that could be me one day!
.
